PharosVPN client for OPNsense (os-pharosvpn)

A GUI plugin that turns an OPNsense firewall into a PharosVPN (caravel) client:
import a .pharos profile, bring up the userspace obfuscated AmneziaWG tunnel, and
route selected LAN sources through it — with policy routing, an optional
kill-switch, and a live status page.

CLIENT MODE only. Server components (node / relay / coxswain) are out of scope.

Provides:
  * A VPN -> PharosVPN menu with Profiles, Connection, and Status pages.
  * Profile import + inspection (resolved nodes / egress path / expiry / fleet),
    with all profile decryption handled by the pharos-awg daemon (no crypto in
    PHP); encrypted-mode payloads stay sealed at rest in config.xml.
  * configd-managed lifecycle, a 'pharosvpn' interface group for pf rules, and
    reconfigure-on-boot persistence.

Depends on the base 'pharosvpn' package (pharos-awg daemon + rc.d).

Status: pre-alpha. The tunnel data plane is verified on the dev VM; full
end-to-end LAN routing through a live fleet node is not yet verified.
